article.headline: High Point 63, Winthrop 56
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. -- Nick Barbour scored 31 points and High Point earned a season sweep over archrival Winthrop with a 63-56 victory on Wednesday night. Barbour, a freshman, also scored 32 points on Saturday in a 70-68 loss to Coastal Carolina. The Panthers (7-17, 3-11 Big South Conference) have won two of their last three games after a 1-11 stretch in which their only win was a 42-40 victory over Winthrop on Jan. 7. The Eagles (6-18, 5-9) have lost five straight. High Point led by as many as 16 at 41-25 with 15:42 left. Winthrop cut the deficit to 60-56 on a three-point play by Cameron Stanley with 2:55 remaining, but didn't score again, missing five straight shots. Besides Barbour, who hit 10 of 20 field goals and 7 of 7 free throws, no other Panthers player scored more than six points. Andre Jones led Winthrop with 14 points.
